Section 1.1: The Memory Subsystem Analogy

The CSS Z-Index Analogy

MemoryRegion tree = CSS z-index stacking

· Nested regions with priorities
· Children overlap parents
· Aliases reference other regions

FlatView = Final rendered DOM

· Flattened, non-overlapping view
· Computed from the tree
· Used for actual memory access

AddressSpace = Browser window

· Contains the rendered view
· Multiple windows (system, I/O, CPU)

