Section 1.3: MemoryRegion Types

The MemoryRegion Family

```c
// include/exec/memory.h

struct MemoryRegion {
    const MemoryRegionOps *ops;   // MMIO callbacks
    void *opaque;                 // Device state
    MemoryRegion *container;      // Parent region
    Int128 size;                  // Size in bytes
    hwaddr addr;                  // Base address within parent
    uint32_t align;               // Alignment
    bool ram;                     // RAM (vs MMIO)
    bool rom;                     // ROM (read-only)
    bool readonly;                // Read-only
    bool nonvolatile;             // NVDIMM
    bool dirty_log_mask;          // Dirty logging (migration, VGA)
    // ...
};
```

MemoryRegion Types

1. RAM

```c
// Backed by host memory (malloc, mmap)
memory_region_init_ram(mr, NULL, "ram", 0x10000000, &error_fatal);
// Fast path: memory_region_get_ram_ptr()
void *hva = memory_region_get_ram_ptr(mr);
```

2. MMIO

```c
// Custom read/write callbacks
static const MemoryRegionOps my_ops = {
    .read = my_read,
    .write = my_write,
    .endianness = DEVICE_LITTLE_ENDIAN,
};
memory_region_init_io(mr, NULL, &my_ops, opaque, "mmio", 0x1000);
// Slow path: function calls per access
```

3. ROM

```c
// Read-only (firmware, BIOS)
memory_region_init_rom(mr, NULL, "bios", 0x100000, &error_fatal);
// Writes are ignored
```

4. ROM Device

```c
// Read-only, but can be written by device
memory_region_init_rom_device(mr, NULL, &my_ops, opaque, "rom-device", 0x1000);
```

5. Alias

```c
// References another region (fragmentation)
memory_region_init_alias(mr, NULL, "alias", target_mr, 0, 0x1000);
// Used for PCI BARs, firmware mapping, etc.
```

6. Container

```c
// Group of regions (subtree)
memory_region_init(mr, NULL, "container", UINT64_MAX);
memory_region_add_subregion(container, 0, subregion1);
memory_region_add_subregion(container, 0x1000, subregion2);
```

7. IOMMU

```c
// Translates addresses (ARM SMMU, x86 IOMMU)
memory_region_init_iommu(mr, &iommu_ops, NULL, "iommu", 0x10000000);
```

