Section 1.4: MemoryRegion Tree Example

PC Machine Memory Map (x86)

```
address_space_memory (root)
├── "pc.ram" (RAM) size=0x10000000 (256MB)
│   └── Guest RAM (host memory)
├── "pc.bios" (ROM) size=0x100000 (1MB)
│   └── BIOS firmware
├── "pc.rom" (ROM) size=0x10000 (64KB)
│   └── Option ROM (boot ROM)
├── "pci" (container) size=0x100000000 (4GB)
│   ├── "pci.0" (PCI bus) size=0x10000000 (256MB)
│   │   ├── "virtio-blk" (MMIO) size=0x1000
│   │   ├── "virtio-net" (MMIO) size=0x1000
│   │   └── "vga" (MMIO) size=0x10000
│   └── "pci.1" (PCIe bus) size=0x10000000 (256MB)
│       └── ...
├── "acpi" (MMIO) size=0x10000
├── "smm" (RAM) size=0x100000 (1MB)
└── "ioapic" (MMIO) size=0x1000
```

Building the Tree

```c
// hw/i386/pc.c - simplified
static void pc_memory_init(MachineState *machine) {
    // 1. Create root
    MemoryRegion *system_memory = get_system_memory();
    
    // 2. Add RAM
    MemoryRegion *ram = g_new(MemoryRegion, 1);
    memory_region_init_ram(ram, NULL, "pc.ram", machine->ram_size, &error_fatal);
    memory_region_add_subregion(system_memory, 0, ram);
    
    // 3. Add BIOS
    MemoryRegion *bios = g_new(MemoryRegion, 1);
    memory_region_init_rom(bios, NULL, "pc.bios", 0x100000, &error_fatal);
    memory_region_add_subregion(system_memory, 0x100000000 - 0x100000, bios);
    
    // 4. Add PCI
    MemoryRegion *pci = g_new(MemoryRegion, 1);
    memory_region_init(pci, NULL, "pci", 0x100000000);
    memory_region_add_subregion(system_memory, 0xE0000000, pci);
    
    // 5. Add PCI devices
    pci_register_device(pci, ...);
}
```

