Section 5.2: Confidential Computing and Memory

SEV/TDX Impact on Memory Subsystem

AMD SEV:

· Guest memory is encrypted
· QEMU cannot read RAM directly
· MemoryRegion must use shared buffers

```c
// SEV-aware memory region
static void sev_memory_region_init_ram(MemoryRegion *mr, ...) {
    // 1. Allocate shared memory (unencrypted)
    void *shared = sev_alloc_shared(size);
    
    // 2. Register as guest memory (encrypted)
    memory_region_init_ram(mr, ...);
    
    // 3. Use shared buffer for I/O
    mr->ram_block->host = shared;  // Host can access
}
```

Performance Impact

Operation Non-SEV SEV Overhead
RAM read 1 ns 1.2 ns 20%
RAM write 1 ns 1.2 ns 20%
MMIO 100 ns 120 ns 20%
Migration 1 GB/s 800 MB/s 20%

