Section 5.3: The Future of Memory Virtualization

CXL Integration

CXL (Compute Express Link):

· Cache-coherent interconnect
· Sub-microsecond latency
· Memory pooling across hosts

Virtio over CXL:

```c
// CXL memory region
static void cxl_memory_region_init(MemoryRegion *mr, ...) {
    // 1. Map CXL memory directly
    void *cxl_ptr = mmap(NULL, size, PROT_READ | PROT_WRITE,
                         MAP_SHARED, cxl_fd, offset);
    
    // 2. Register with QEMU (no copy!)
    memory_region_init_ram_ptr(mr, NULL, "cxl-memory", size, cxl_ptr);
    
    // 3. Guest can access CXL memory directly
