Q33: How does VFIO use MemoryListener?

<details>
<summary><b>Answer</b></summary>

VFIO registers a listener for DMA regions. When a MemoryRegion is added, VFIO maps it for DMA (using VFIO_IOMMU_MAP_DMA). This allows the passthrough device to access guest memory via DMA.

</details>

Q34: What is the memory region coalescing?

<details>
<summary><b>Answer</b></summary>

Coalescing merges adjacent FlatRanges into one range. Used in FlatView generation to reduce the number of ranges. Improves cache efficiency and lookup time.

</details>

Q35: How would you implement persistent memory in QEMU?

