Q36: What is the role of MemoryRegionSection in listeners?

<details>
<summary><b>Answer</b></summary>

MemoryRegionSection is the unit of change in listeners. It contains the region, offset, and size. Listeners use it to update their own memory maps (e.g., KVM slots, VFIO DMA mappings).

